%% FIGURE U6 — Subscription Transfer Sequence Diagram
%% Patent: System and Method for Multi-Agent AI Orchestration
%% Sequence diagram for Claim 3(f) — Subscription Transfer on Agent Restart

sequenceDiagram
    participant Agent as Agent Process
    participant System as Orchestration<br/>Engine
    participant Store as Persistent<br/>Data Store
    participant Board as Message<br/>Board

    Note over Agent,Board: PHASE 1: Normal Operation (Pre-Restart)

    Agent->>Board: Post message (session: old-id)
    Board->>Store: Append message (ID: 47)
    Note right of Store: Agent subscriber record:<br/>session_id = "old-id"<br/>last_read_id = 47

    Note over Agent,Board: PHASE 2: Agent Process Interruption

    Agent--xAgent: Process terminates<br/>(crash, restart, or wake)

    Note over Agent,Board: Messages arrive while agent is offline

    rect rgb(70, 70, 100)
        Note over Board,Store: Messages posted by other agents
        Board->>Store: Message ID: 48 (from Agent B)
        Board->>Store: Message ID: 49 (from Agent C)
        Board->>Store: Message ID: 50 (from Agent B)
    end

    Note right of Store: Messages 48-50 accumulate<br/>Agent's cursor still at 47

    Note over Agent,Board: PHASE 3: Agent Restart & Subscription Transfer

    System->>System: Spawn new agent process<br/>in stored execution environment
    System->>System: Assign new session ID: "new-id"

    System->>Store: Transfer subscription:<br/>("old-id" → "new-id")

    activate Store
    Store->>Store: Create new subscriber record:<br/>session_id = "new-id"<br/>last_read_id = 47<br/>(cursor preserved!)
    Store->>Store: Delete old subscriber record:<br/>session_id = "old-id"
    deactivate Store

    Store-->>System: Transfer complete

    System->>Agent: Re-transmit stored<br/>behavior prompt

    Note over Agent,Board: PHASE 4: Resumed Operation — Catch-Up Read

    Agent->>Board: Read request (session: new-id)
    Board->>Store: Query: messages WHERE<br/>id > 47 AND sender ≠ new-id
    Store-->>Board: Return messages 48, 49, 50

    Board->>Store: Update cursor:<br/>new-id → last_read_id = 50
    Board-->>Agent: Deliver messages 48, 49, 50

    Note over Agent,Board: Agent has received all messages<br/>posted during downtime —<br/>no duplicates, no losses,<br/>cursor continuity maintained

    Agent->>Board: Post reply (session: new-id, ID: 51)
    Note right of Store: Normal operation resumed<br/>with new session ID
